            <title>[FLINK-13353] Remove 2 args constructor in REPLACE expression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-13353</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Replace definition in stringExpression.scala has another constructor with 2 arguments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to source code, the args&apos; meaning are str, begin. And it call other constructor with 3 args adding the 3rd arg which is the length of str.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But its expectTypes is (String, String, String), but actually is (String, int, int).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think the 2 args defined constructor means search and replacement is &quot;&quot; default, not begin and length of str.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
